President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his Administration. 

1. John Cotton Richmond of Virginia is nominated to be the Director of the Office to Monitor and Combat Trafficking at the Department of State. He is the founder of the Human Trafficking Institute and has previously served as the Special Litigation Counsel with the Civil Rights Division of the Department of Justice. He has also worked at the International Justice Mission in India and has received awards for his work in human trafficking investigations.

2. Kathleen Ann Kavalec of California is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Albania. She currently serves as Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of European and Eurasian Affairs at the Department of State and has over three decades of experience as an American diplomat. She is fluent in multiple languages including French, Romanian, Ukrainian, Russian, Spanish, and Portuguese.

3. Francisco Luis Palmieri of Connecticut is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Honduras. He currently serves as Acting Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of Western Hemisphere Affairs at the Department of State and has over thirty years of experience as an American diplomat. He has held senior leadership positions within the Department of State domestically and has also served at five U.S. Missions overseas. He is fluent in Spanish.